API to work with Helios Nephrite

API and SDK Documentation

Version: 1.0
Swagger with ASP.NET Core API of Helios Nephrite. (version: 6.0.22-rc)

Configuration

apiV1ConfigurationPeriodsGet

Gets record periods defined in configuration. According to periodQueryParams currently active periods can be returned as well.


/api/v1/Configuration/Periods

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android

import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;

import java.util.*;

public class ConfigurationApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        // Configure HTTP basic authorization: basicAuth
        HttpBasicAuth basicAuth = (HttpBasicAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("basicAuth");
        basicAuth.setUsername("YOUR USERNAME");
        basicAuth.setPassword("YOUR PASSWORD");

        ConfigurationApi apiInstance = new ConfigurationApi();
        RecordPeriodKind periodKind = ; // RecordPeriodKind | Kind of period to get.
        RecordPeriodRange periodRange = ; // RecordPeriodRange | Range of period to get.
        try {
            RecordPeriodResponse result = apiInstance.apiV1ConfigurationPeriodsGet(periodKind, periodRange);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ConfigurationApi#apiV1ConfigurationPeriodsGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Configuration *apiConfig = [Configuration sharedConfig];
// Configure HTTP basic authorization (authentication scheme: basicAuth)
[apiConfig setUsername:@"YOUR_USERNAME"];
[apiConfig setPassword:@"YOUR_PASSWORD"];
RecordPeriodKind *periodKind = ; // Kind of period to get. (optional)
RecordPeriodRange *periodRange = ; // Range of period to get. (optional)

ConfigurationApi *apiInstance = [[ConfigurationApi alloc] init];

// Gets record periods defined in configuration. According to periodQueryParams currently active periods can be returned as well.
[apiInstance apiV1ConfigurationPeriodsGetWith:periodKind
    periodRange:periodRange
              completionHandler: ^(RecordPeriodResponse output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using IO.Swagger.Api;
using IO.Swagger.Client;
using IO.Swagger.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class apiV1ConfigurationPeriodsGetExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            // Configure HTTP basic authorization: basicAuth
            Configuration.Default.Username = "YOUR_USERNAME";
            Configuration.Default.Password = "YOUR_PASSWORD";

            var apiInstance = new ConfigurationApi();
            var periodKind = new RecordPeriodKind(); // RecordPeriodKind | Kind of period to get. (optional) 
            var periodRange = new RecordPeriodRange(); // RecordPeriodRange | Range of period to get. (optional) 

            try
            {
                // Gets record periods defined in configuration. According to periodQueryParams currently active periods can be returned as well.
                RecordPeriodResponse result = apiInstance.apiV1ConfigurationPeriodsGet(periodKind, periodRange);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }
            catch (Exception e)
            {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling ConfigurationApi.apiV1ConfigurationPeriodsGet: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

Connect

apiConnectLogInPost

<br> Authorizes the user specified in the authenticateInfo parameter. <br> Each call to this endpoint causes a new session to be created on the application server. To authorize endpoints that require a basic authorization, you must use the returned values "UserName" as the login name and "UserId" as the password.

Sample request with a HeN account: ``` POST /api/connect/login HTTP/1.1 Host: localhost:53078 Content-Type: application/json { "username": "username", "password": "password", "LanguageId" : "CZ", "DbProfile": "test_env", "ServerURL" : "http://www.mydomain.cz/hen" } ``` Sample request with a domain account: ``` POST /api/connect/login HTTP/1.1 Host: localhost:53078 Content-Type: application/json { "username": "ASOL\\username", "password": "domain password", "UseWindowsAuthentication": true, "UseCurrentUserCredentials": false "LanguageId" : "CZ", "DbProfile": "test_env", "ServerURL" : "http://www.mydomain.cz/hen" } ```


/api/Connect/LogIn

Responses

Status: 200 - <br> Returns info of authenticated user: <br> ``` { "success": true, "statusCode": 200, "errorMessage": "", "userName": "ASOL\\username", "userId": "UserId 31f49a7ddc18e97247308d5180ac684890f5a5c3442e0ab7115e037f6d6dd2f6" } ``` <br> Use returned "userName" value as user name and "userId" value as password for following basic authorization for requests that require an authentication then.

  • Schema

Status: 400 - <br> If authorization failed: <br> ``` { "type": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.5.1", "title": "BadRequest", "status": 400, "detail": "Application server connection credentials are not valid.", "instance": "POST /api/Connect/LogIn", } ```

  • Schema

Status: 403 - Forbidden

  • Schema

Status: 422 - Client Error

  • Schema

Status: 500 - <br> If an unexpected error occurred. Check the log then. <br> ``` { "type": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7235#section...", "title": "InternalServerError", "status": 500, "detail": ""Unknown error, check the log, please."", "instance": "POST /api/Connect/LogIn", } ```

  • Schema

Status: 503 - Server Error

apiConnectLogOutPost

Logs out currently authorized user and removes it from authenticated users.


/api/Connect/LogOut

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python

 -H "Authorization: Basic [[basicHash]]"\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
"//api/Connect/LogOut"
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ConnectApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ConnectApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        // Configure HTTP basic authorization: basicAuth
        HttpBasicAuth basicAuth = (HttpBasicAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("basicAuth");
        basicAuth.setUsername("YOUR USERNAME");
        basicAuth.setPassword("YOUR PASSWORD");

        ConnectApi apiInstance = new ConnectApi();
        try {
            User result = apiInstance.apiConnectLogOutPost();
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ConnectApi#apiConnectLogOutPost");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

DataTransfers

apiV1DataTransfersExportsBrowseAuthorSymbolicNameClassSymbolicNamePdfPost

Exports records to PDF via a default browse base template. A default browse base template is either a template of an implicit view of a current user if it is defined, or a default browse base template for a class. An optional collection of records to export can be specified in a payload. A class of records, as well as the class of a folder, filter, template, etc. corresponds to the class in the route parameters authorSymbolicName/classSymbolicName. If the default browse base template contains inner filter that contains any parameter, its name and have to be specified in a payload.


/api/v1/DataTransfers/Exports/Browse/{AuthorSymbolicName}/{classSymbolicName}/Pdf

        String classSymbolicName = classSymbolicName_example; // String | Symbolic name of a class.
        ExportFilePdfBrowseRequest body = ; // ExportFilePdfBrowseRequest | Payload of the request.
        array[String] aSOLWebAPIPeriod = ; // array[String] | 

            If this header is specified, request will be processed in context of specified period(s). 
            More headers with this name may be specified to set more kinds of period in one call.
            


            Values of standard period kinds can be:
            

            Accounting=0x0000000100000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000
            Calendar=0x0000000080000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000
            
The hex string is a code of period.

            Values of custom period kinds uses a syntax like: 
            

            Custom|HumanResources=2022-02-01T00:00:00Z
            
It means the code of period is composite one. First "Custom" key must be specified and after separator char ('|') is the custom period code itself.

            To get period codes call GET /api/v{N}/Configuration/Periods endpoint.

Responses

// Exports records to PDF via a default browse base template. 
A default browse base template is either a template of an implicit view of a current user if it is defined,
or a default browse base template for a class.

An optional collection of records to export can be specified in a payload.
A class of records, as well as the class of a folder, filter, template, etc. corresponds to the class in the route parameter classId.

If the default browse base template contains inner filter that contains any parameter, its name and have to be specified in a payload.

Responses

Status: 200 - Records was exported to PDF file and the file was returned in response body as content. The content-type is "application/pdf" and the suggested file name is returned in Content-Disposition header.

apiV1DataTransfersExportsBrowseClassSymbolicNamePdfPost

Exports records to PDF via a default browse base template. A default browse base template is either a template of an implicit view of a current user if it is defined, or a default browse base template for a class. An optional collection of records to export can be specified in a payload. A class of records, as well as the class of a folder, filter, template, etc. corresponds to the class in the route parameter classSymbolicName. If the default browse base template contains inner filter that contains any parameter, its name and have to be specified in a payload.


/api/v1/DataTransfers/Exports/Browse/{classSymbolicName}/Pdf

apiV1DataTransfersExportsBrowseReportsReportIdPdfPost

Exports records to PDF via a browse report. An optional collection of records to export can be specified in a payload. A class of records, as well as the class of a folder, filter, etc. corresponds to the class of the report that is specified in the route parameter reportId. If the report contains any parameter, its name and value have to be specified in a payload.


/api/v1/DataTransfers/Exports/BrowseReports/{reportId}/Pdf

Responses

apiV1DataTransfersGeneralImportIdPost

Function which imports data in file specified in functionQuerySettings parameter (ASOL.WebAPI.Core.DataTransfers.Contracts.GeneralImportFunctionQuery.FileUID). First file has to be uploaded by one of endpoint on route /api/v1/Files/. Those endpoints return a unique file identifier, which has to be passed to this endpoint.


/api/v1/DataTransfers/GeneralImport/{id}

        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        // Configure HTTP basic authorization: basicAuth
        HttpBasicAuth basicAuth = (HttpBasicAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("basicAuth");
        basicAuth.setUsername("YOUR USERNAME");
        basicAuth.setPassword("YOUR PASSWORD");

        DocumentsApi apiInstance = new DocumentsApi();
        String fileName = fileName_example; // String | Physical name of file.


Including the '%' character in the parameter value causes the comparison operator "LIKE" to be used instead of "EQUALS"

        Double version = 1.2; // Double | Version of document.
        String state = state_example; // String | State of document (custom valuated attribute, it may differ for every customer).
Use data values of a defined attribute valuation to query documents of the requested state.
        String reference = reference_example; // String | A reference code of document.


Including the '%' character in the parameter value causes the comparison operator "LIKE" to be used instead of "EQUALS"

        String name = name_example; // String | Name of a document. 


Including the '%' character in the parameter value causes the comparison operator "LIKE" to be used instead of "EQUALS"

        Integer skip = 56; // Integer | Number of rows which are skipped during retrieval of data.
If not specified, no rows are skipped. It means, the first row on the first page is displayed at the top of the page.
        Integer top = 56; // Integer | Page size.
If not specified, 100 is used
        Integer folderId = 56; // Integer | Folder identifier where to get documents from. If not set, a condition on a folder will not be applied.
        Long timestamp = 789; // Long | If set, documents with timestamps greater than this timestamp are returned.
        Boolean fileContent = true; // Boolean | If true, content of external document is returned too. Default true.
        try {
            DMSDocumentsResult result = apiInstance.apiV1DocumentsDMSDocumentsGet(fileName, version, state, reference, name, skip, top, folderId, timestamp, fileContent);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling DocumentsApi#apiV1DocumentsDMSDocumentsGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

public class DocumentsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        // Configure HTTP basic authorization: basicAuth
        HttpBasicAuth basicAuth = (HttpBasicAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("basicAuth");
        basicAuth.setUsername("YOUR USERNAME");
        basicAuth.setPassword("YOUR PASSWORD");

        DocumentsApi apiInstance = new DocumentsApi();
        String fileName = fileName_example; // String | Name of file.


Including the '%' character in the parameter value causes the comparison operator "LIKE" to be used instead of "EQUALS"

        String state = state_example; // String | State of document (custom valuated attribute, it may differ for every customer).
Use data values of a defined attribute valuation to query documents of the requested state.
        ExtDocLocation location = ; // ExtDocLocation | Location of external document.
        String reference = reference_example; // String | A reference code of document.


Including the '%' character in the parameter value causes the comparison operator "LIKE" to be used instead of "EQUALS"

        String name = name_example; // String | Name of a document. 


Including the '%' character in the parameter value causes the comparison operator "LIKE" to be used instead of "EQUALS"

        Integer skip = 56; // Integer | Number of rows which are skipped during retrieval of data.
If not specified, no rows are skipped. It means, the first row on the first page is displayed at the top of the page.
        Integer top = 56; // Integer | Page size.
If not specified, 100 is used
        Integer folderId = 56; // Integer | Folder identifier where to get documents from. If not set, a condition on a folder will not be applied.
        Long timestamp = 789; // Long | If set, documents with timestamps greater than this timestamp are returned.
        Boolean fileContent = true; // Boolean | If true, content of external document is returned too. Default true.
        try {
            ExternalDocumentsResult result = apiInstance.apiV1DocumentsExternalDocumentsGet(fileName, state, location, reference, name, skip, top, folderId, timestamp, fileContent);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling DocumentsApi#apiV1DocumentsExternalDocumentsGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.DocumentsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class DocumentsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        // Configure HTTP basic authorization: basicAuth
        HttpBasicAuth basicAuth = (HttpBasicAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("basicAuth");
        basicAuth.setUsername("YOUR USERNAME");
        basicAuth.setPassword("YOUR PASSWORD");

        DocumentsApi apiInstance = new DocumentsApi();
        String fileName = fileName_example; // String | Physical name of file.


Including the '%' character in the parameter value causes the comparison operator "LIKE" to be used instead of "EQUALS"

        String reference = reference_example; // String | A reference code of document.


Including the '%' character in the parameter value causes the comparison operator "LIKE" to be used instead of "EQUALS"

        String name = name_example; // String | Name of a document. 


Including the '%' character in the parameter value causes the comparison operator "LIKE" to be used instead of "EQUALS"

        Integer skip = 56; // Integer | Number of rows which are skipped during retrieval of data.
If not specified, no rows are skipped. It means, the first row on the first page is displayed at the top of the page.
        Integer top = 56; // Integer | Page size.
If not specified, 100 is used
        Integer folderId = 56; // Integer | Folder identifier where to get documents from. If not set, a condition on a folder will not be applied.
        Long timestamp = 789; // Long | If set, documents with timestamps greater than this timestamp are returned.
        Boolean fileContent = true; // Boolean | If true, content of external document is returned too. Default true.
        try {
            ManagedDocumentsResult result = apiInstance.apiV1DocumentsManagedDocumentsGet(fileName, reference, name, skip, top, folderId, timestamp, fileContent);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling DocumentsApi#apiV1DocumentsManagedDocumentsGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Files

apiV1FilesUploadLargeFilePost

Uploads a file to the WebAPI server temp directory. File size limit is 1 GB. File is passed as "multipart/form-data", however body with those file is read by a stream reader continuously. Beware! Uploaded file is kept limited time only! See query parameters for more information.


/api/v1/Files/UploadLargeFile

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python

 -H "Authorization: Basic [[basicHash]]"\
-H "Accept: application/json"\

apiV1FilesUploadLargeFileToHeliosPost

Uploads a file to the Helios Nephrite application server temp directory ("Upload"). File size limit is 1 GB. File is passed as "multipart/form-data", however body with those file is read by a stream reader continuously.


/api/v1/Files/UploadLargeFileToHelios

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X POST\
 -H "Authorization: Basic [[basicHash]]"\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
"//api/v1/Files/UploadLargeFileToHelios?CheckCrc="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.FilesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class FilesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        // Configure HTTP basic authorization: basicAuth
        HttpBasicAuth basicAuth = (HttpBasicAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("basicAuth");
        basicAuth.setUsername("YOUR USERNAME");
        basicAuth.setPassword("YOUR PASSWORD");

        FilesApi apiInstance = new FilesApi();
        Boolean checkCrc = true; // Boolean | If true, content CRC of an uploaded file is checked while uploading file to Helios Nephrite application server.
        try {
            UploadedFileResult result = apiInstance.apiV1FilesUploadLargeFileToHeliosPost(checkCrc);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FilesApi#apiV1FilesUploadLargeFileToHeliosPost");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

apiV1FilesUploadMoreFilesPost

Uploads files to the WebAPI server temp directory. Beware! Uploaded files are kept limited time only! See query parameters for more information.


/api/v1/Files/UploadMoreFiles

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.FilesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class FilesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        // Configure HTTP basic authorization: basicAuth
        HttpBasicAuth basicAuth = (HttpBasicAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("basicAuth");
        basicAuth.setUsername("YOUR USERNAME");
        basicAuth.setPassword("YOUR PASSWORD");

        FilesApi apiInstance = new FilesApi();
        array[byte[]] files = ; // array[byte[]] | 
        CacheItemPriority priority = ; // CacheItemPriority | The priority for keeping the cache entry in the cache during a memory pressure tokened cleanup. Possible values: low, normal, high, neverRemove.
        Integer absoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = 56; // Integer | Defines an absolute expiration time (in minutes), relative to time when a cache entry was stored.
        Integer slidingExpiration = 56; // Integer | Defines how long (in minutes) the cache entry can be inactive (e.g. not accessed) before it will be removed. 
This will not extend the entry lifetime beyond the absolute expiration (if set).
        try {
            UploadFilesCollectionResult{UploadedFileResult} result = apiInstance.apiV1FilesUploadMoreFilesPost(files, priority, absoluteExpirationRelativeToNow, slidingExpiration);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FilesApi#apiV1FilesUploadMoreFilesPost");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.FilesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class FilesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        // Configure HTTP basic authorization: basicAuth
        HttpBasicAuth basicAuth = (HttpBasicAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("basicAuth");
        basicAuth.setUsername("YOUR USERNAME");
        basicAuth.setPassword("YOUR PASSWORD");

        FilesApi apiInstance = new FilesApi();
        array[byte[]] files = ; // array[byte[]] | 
        Boolean checkCrc = true; // Boolean | If true, content CRC of an uploaded file is checked while uploading file to Helios Nephrite application server.
        try {
            UploadFilesCollectionResult{UploadedFileResult} result = apiInstance.apiV1FilesUploadMoreFilesToHeliosPost(files, checkCrc);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FilesApi#apiV1FilesUploadMoreFilesToHeliosPost");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Configuration *apiConfig = [Configuration sharedConfig];
// Configure HTTP basic authorization (authentication scheme: basicAuth)
[apiConfig setUsername:@"YOUR_USERNAME"];
[apiConfig setPassword:@"YOUR_PASSWORD"];
array[byte[]] *files = ; //  (optional)
Boolean *checkCrc = true; // If true, content CRC of an uploaded file is checked while uploading file to Helios Nephrite application server. (optional)

FilesApi *apiInstance = [[FilesApi alloc] init];

// Uploads files to the Helios Nephrite application server temp directory ("Upload").
[apiInstance apiV1FilesUploadMoreFilesToHeliosPostWith:files
    checkCrc:checkCrc
              completionHandler: ^(UploadFilesCollectionResult{UploadedFileResult} output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

var ApiToWorkWithHeliosNephrite = require('api_to_work_with_helios_nephrite');
var defaultClient = ApiToWorkWithHeliosNephrite.ApiClient.instance;
// Configure HTTP basic authorization: basicAuth
var basicAuth = defaultClient.authentications['basicAuth'];
basicAuth.username = 'YOUR USERNAME'
basicAuth.password = 'YOUR PASSWORD'

var api = new ApiToWorkWithHeliosNephrite.FilesApi()
var opts = { 
  'files':  // {{array[byte[]]}} 
  'checkCrc': true // {{Boolean}} If true, content CRC of an uploaded file is checked while uploading file to Helios Nephrite application server.
};
var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.apiV1FilesUploadMoreFilesToHeliosPost(opts, callback);

            {

apiV1FilesUploadPost

Uploads a file to the Web API server temp directory. Beware! Uploaded file is kept limited time only! See query parameters for more information.


/api/v1/Files/Upload

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.FilesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class FilesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        // Configure HTTP basic authorization: basicAuth
        HttpBasicAuth basicAuth = (HttpBasicAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("basicAuth");
        basicAuth.setUsername("YOUR USERNAME");
        basicAuth.setPassword("YOUR PASSWORD");

        FilesApi apiInstance = new FilesApi();
        byte[] file = file_example; // byte[] | 
        CacheItemPriority priority = ; // CacheItemPriority | The priority for keeping the cache entry in the cache during a memory pressure tokened cleanup. Possible values: low, normal, high, neverRemove.
        Integer absoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = 56; // Integer | Defines an absolute expiration time (in minutes), relative to time when a cache entry was stored.
        Integer slidingExpiration = 56; // Integer | Defines how long (in minutes) the cache entry can be inactive (e.g. not accessed) before it will be removed. 
This will not extend the entry lifetime beyond the absolute expiration (if set).
        try {
            UploadedFileResult result = apiInstance.apiV1FilesUploadPost(file, priority, absoluteExpirationRelativeToNow, slidingExpiration);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FilesApi#apiV1FilesUploadPost");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

            var absoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = 56;  // Integer | Defines an absolute expiration time (in minutes), relative to time when a cache entry was stored. (optional) 
            var slidingExpiration = 56;  // Integer | Defines how long (in minutes) the cache entry can be inactive (e.g. not accessed) before it will be removed.

Type
BrowseType
<br> Type of a browse. Default is ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.Contracts.BrowseType.Template.
Filter
String
<br> Filter expression to get data. <br> THIS PROPERTY'S NOT SUPPORTED YET! DON'T USE IT AT ALL! IT IS IGNORED! INSTEAD, USE A PREDEFINED FILTER (ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.Contracts.QueryParameters.BrowseQueryParameters.FilterId) or filter which is a part of a browse template (ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.Contracts.QueryParameters.BrowseQueryParameters.Id).
FilterId
Integer (int32)
Unique identifier of a predefined filter to get data.
FilterParams
array[String]
<br>Optional. It has to be specified when a filter definition (ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.Contracts.QueryParameters.BrowseQueryParameters.FilterId) contains variable arguments. <br> Variable arguments of a filter which is specified in ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.Contracts.QueryParameters.BrowseQueryParameters.FilterId. They have to be specified when this filter contains at least one parameter which value is specified as a variable (a named parameter). This value has to be specified at the moment when the filter is applied. If value of parameter is not set, it will be marked as skipped, see Description in example. If value is null, a null value will be passed to parameter. <br> Example: ?FilterParams=Code='ABC'&FilterParams=Price=123.56&FilterParams=issueDate=2021-11-03T00:00:00&FilterParams=Description&FilterParams=Code=null
TemplateFilterParams
array[String]
<br>Optional. It has to be specified when a browse template filter definition (ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.Contracts.QueryParameters.BrowseQueryParameters.Id) contains variable arguments. <br> Variable arguments of a filter which is part of a browse template filter definition (default one for a current user or specified in ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.Contracts.QueryParameters.BrowseQueryParameters.Id). They have to be specified when this filter contains at least one parameter which value is specified as a variable (a named parameter). This value has to be specified at the moment when the filter is applied. If value of parameter is not set, it will be marked as skipped, see Description in example. If value is null, a null value will be passed to parameter. <br> Example: TemplateFilterParams=Code='ABC'&TemplateFilterParams=Price=123.56&TemplateFilterParams=issueDate=2021-11-03T00:00:00&TemplateFilterParams=Description&TemplateFilterParams=Code=null
OrderBy
String
Sort order rules for returned data. Rules have to match a column definition of template which is used to retrieve data. Format is: "[template column name] [sort direction]", e.g.: ?orderBy=name desc,hireDate. Also "asc" can be used for more clarity. If neither "desc" nor "asc" is used, "asc" is used by default.
TotalCount
Boolean
Gets or sets if ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.Contracts.BrowseResponse should contain the total number of rows. Default is false.
Count
Boolean
Gets or sets if ASOL.Nephrite.WebAPI.Contracts.BrowseResponse should contain the number of rows on current page.. Default is true.
Skip
Integer (int32)
Number of rows which are skipped during retrieval of data. If not specified, no rows are skipped. It means, the first row on the first page is displayed at the top of the page.
Top
Integer (int32)
Page size. If not specified, default user settings will be used.

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.PantheonApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class PantheonApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        // Configure HTTP basic authorization: basicAuth
        HttpBasicAuth basicAuth = (HttpBasicAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("basicAuth");
        basicAuth.setUsername("YOUR USERNAME");
        basicAuth.setPassword("YOUR PASSWORD");

        PantheonApi apiInstance = new PantheonApi();
        Integer mistnostId = 56; // Integer | CZ: Id majetku.
        String mistnost.MistnostCislo = mistnost.MistnostCislo_example; // String | 
        String mistnost.MistnostNazev = mistnost.MistnostNazev_example; // String | 
        String zodpovednaOsoba.OsobniCislo = zodpovednaOsoba.OsobniCislo_example; // String | 
        String zodpovednaOsoba.Login = zodpovednaOsoba.Login_example; // String | 
        String zodpovednaOsoba.Jmeno = zodpovednaOsoba.Jmeno_example; // String | 
        String zodpovednaOsoba.Prijmeni = zodpovednaOsoba.Prijmeni_example; // String | 
        Integer zodpovednaOsobaId = 56; // Integer | 
        Integer typMajetku = 56; // Integer | 
        try {
            FixedAssetGetResponse result = apiInstance.apiV1CustomerPantheonMajetekGet(mistnostId, mistnost.MistnostCislo, mistnost.MistnostNazev, zodpovednaOsoba.OsobniCislo, zodpovednaOsoba.Login, zodpovednaOsoba.Jmeno, zodpovednaOsoba.Prijmeni, zodpovednaOsobaId, typMajetku);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling PantheonApi#apiV1CustomerPantheonMajetekGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import io.swagger.client.api.PantheonApi;

public class PantheonApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        HttpBasicAuth basicAuth = (HttpBasicAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("basicAuth");
        basicAuth.setUsername("YOUR USERNAME");
        basicAuth.setPassword("YOUR PASSWORD");

        PantheonApi apiInstance = new PantheonApi();
        Integer kodKnihy = 56; // Integer | CZ: Kód knihy poplatku
        Integer platceId = 56; // Integer | CZ: Interní identifikátor Plátce (parametr má přednost před ostatními parametry)
        String platceIdEx = platceIdEx_example; // String | CZ: Externí identifikátor Plátce (parametr má přednost před ostatními parametry)
        String variabilniSymbol = variabilniSymbol_example; // String | CZ: Variabilní symbol
        String rodneCislo = rodneCislo_example; // String | CZ: Rodné číslo
        String cisloDokladu = cisloDokladu_example; // String | CZ: Číslo dokladu (max. 30 znaků)
        String typDokladu = typDokladu_example; // String | CZ: Typ dokladu - občanský průkaz (O) nebo cestovní pas (C)
        String datumNarozeni = datumNarozeni_example; // String | CZ: Datum narození (formát rrrr-mm-dd)
        String dic = dic_example; // String | CZ: DIČ
        String ico = ico_example; // String | CZ: IČ
        String jmeno = jmeno_example; // String | CZ: Jméno
        String prijmeni = prijmeni_example; // String | CZ: Příjmení
        String nazevDoplnujici = nazevDoplnujici_example; // String | CZ: Název doplňující
        String nazevOrganizace = nazevOrganizace_example; // String | CZ: Název organizace
        String organizaceIdEx = organizaceIdEx_example; // String | CZ: Externí identifikátor organizace
        String adresa.Ulice = adresa.Ulice_example; // String | Nazev ulice
        String adresa.Obec = adresa.Obec_example; // String | Název obce
        String adresa.Psc = adresa.Psc_example; // String | PSČ
        String adresa.CastObce = adresa.CastObce_example; // String | Část obce
        Integer adresa.CisloCp = 56; // Integer | Číslo popisné (domovní)
        Integer adresa.CisloCo = 56; // Integer | Cislo orientacni

            PayerGetResponse result = apiInstance.apiV1CustomerPantheonPlatceGet(kodKnihy, platceId, platceIdEx, variabilniSymbol, rodneCislo, cisloDokladu, typDokladu, datumNarozeni, dic, ico, jmeno, prijmeni, nazevDoplnujici, nazevOrganizace, organizaceIdEx, adresa.Ulice, adresa.Obec, adresa.Psc, adresa.CastObce, adresa.CisloCp, adresa.CisloCo, adresa.PismenoCo, adresa.IdCentralniReg, adresa.TypAdresy, adresa.TypCislaDomovniho, adresa.MestskyObvod, adresa.Okres, adresa.StavAdresy);

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.PantheonApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class PantheonApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        // Configure HTTP basic authorization: basicAuth
        HttpBasicAuth basicAuth = (HttpBasicAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("basicAuth");
        basicAuth.setUsername("YOUR USERNAME");
        basicAuth.setPassword("YOUR PASSWORD");

        PantheonApi apiInstance = new PantheonApi();
        Integer dobropisId = 56; // Integer | 
        String dobropisIdEx = dobropisIdEx_example; // String | 
        String organizace.NazevDoplnujici = organizace.NazevDoplnujici_example; // String | 
        String organizace.Jmeno = organizace.Jmeno_example; // String | 
        String organizace.Prijmeni = organizace.Prijmeni_example; // String | 
        String organizace.Ico = organizace.Ico_example; // String | 
        String organizace.NazevOrganizace = organizace.NazevOrganizace_example; // String | 
        String organizace.Dic = organizace.Dic_example; // String | 
        String organizace.PravniForma = organizace.PravniForma_example; // String | 
        Date organizace.DatumNarozeni = 2013-10-20T19:20:30+01:00; // Date | 
        String organizace.RodneCislo = organizace.RodneCislo_example; // String | 
        String organizace.OrganizaceIdEx = organizace.OrganizaceIdEx_example; // String | 
        String organizace.CisloDokladu = organizace.CisloDokladu_example; // String | CZ: Číslo dokladu
        String organizace.TypDokladu = organizace.TypDokladu_example; // String | CZ: Typ dokladu
        String variabilniSymbol = variabilniSymbol_example; // String | 
        try {
            PaymentGetResponse result = apiInstance.apiV1CustomerPantheonUhradaDobropisGet(dobropisId, dobropisIdEx, organizace.NazevDoplnujici, organizace.Jmeno, organizace.Prijmeni, organizace.Ico, organizace.NazevOrganizace, organizace.Dic, organizace.PravniForma, organizace.DatumNarozeni, organizace.RodneCislo, organizace.OrganizaceIdEx, organizace.CisloDokladu, organizace.TypDokladu, variabilniSymbol);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling PantheonApi#apiV1CustomerPantheonUhradaDobropisGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
